 when (targetState) {
 ScrollDirection.Left -> {
 slideInVertically { -it } togetherWith slideOutVertically { it }
 }
 ScrollDirection.Right -> {
 slideInVertically { it } togetherWith slideOutVertically { -it }
 }
 else -> {
 slideInVertically { 0 } togetherWith slideOutVertically { 0 }
 }
 }
}
```

2. **Proper animation directions**:
 - **Left scroll**: Content slides in from bottom (`-it`) and out to top (`it`)
 - **Right scroll**: Content slides in from top (`it`) and out to bottom (`-it`)
 - **Idle state**: No animation (`0`)

3. **Used the lambda parameter** to satisfy the linter by incorporating it into the modifier chain.

### **How it works now:**

- When scrolling **right** (`ScrollDirection.Right`): The card content animates with a vertical slide from top to bottom
- When scrolling **left** (`ScrollDirection.Left`): The card content animates with a vertical slide from bottom to top 
- When **idle** (`ScrollDirection.Idle`): No animation occurs

